The paper investigates the abandonment and survival of open source projects, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The mixed-methods approach used in the study involves data analysis and a survey, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and systems and control (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper discusses the motivation and difficulties faced by new maintainers, which could be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
